The drawing comes from a 14th-century manuscript known as the Smithfield Decretals . 
  It appears to show the Jedi knight Yoda on the pages of a religious document . 
  But in fact it is part of a bizarre representation of the Biblical story of Samson . 
  The drawing shows a cloaked creature with long, spiky hands and pointy ears . 
  It is from a collection of papal letters and church decrees . 
  British Library curator Julian Harrison said the image is simply a whimsical addition to the manuscript . 
 